{
    "publish_date": "2014-12-27T17:43:50.000Z", 
    "video_length": "PT7M", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "(Destin) Looks good to me.", 
            "dur": "1.1", 
            "start": "0.392"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Nice.", 
            "dur": "1.08", 
            "start": "2.712"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Hey it&#39;s me Destin, welcome back to Smarter Every Day.", 
            "dur": "2.698", 
            "start": "3.792"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So I&#39;m gonna show you something today that&#39;s fascinating.", 
            "dur": "2.027", 
            "start": "6.49"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you take a normal piece of dry spaghetti.", 
            "dur": "2.724", 
            "start": "8.517"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you can do this in your home,", 
            "dur": "1.08", 
            "start": "11.241"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and you bend it right up until the point it breaks,", 
            "dur": "2.467", 
            "start": "12.321"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it doesn&#39;t do what you think it should.", 
            "dur": "2.21", 
            "start": "14.788"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It doesn&#39;t break into two pieces, it breaks into three.", 
            "dur": "3.626", 
            "start": "16.998"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It happens almost every time. You see that?", 
            "dur": "3.012", 
            "start": "20.624"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That broke out of the middle.", 
            "dur": "1.223", 
            "start": "23.636"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Today on Smarter Every Day we&#39;re gonna wait till the kids", 
            "dur": "1.792", 
            "start": "24.859"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "finish their dinner and then we&#39;re gonna break out the", 
            "dur": "2.149", 
            "start": "26.651"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Phantom V1610 and record this at a quarter million frames per second.", 
            "dur": "3.62", 
            "start": "28.8"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And we&#39;re gonna unravel the secret of why spaghetti", 
            "dur": "3.524", 
            "start": "32.42"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "shatters the way it does.", 
            "dur": "2.174", 
            "start": "35.944"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You&#39;re getting Smarter Every Day.", 
            "dur": "1.195", 
            "start": "38.118"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[music]", 
            "dur": "1.11", 
            "start": "39.695"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you haven&#39;t already run to the kitchen", 
            "dur": "1.532", 
            "start": "43.9"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "do that now. Grab some spaghetti and goggle up,", 
            "dur": "2.857", 
            "start": "45.432"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "cause science is about to happen.", 
            "dur": "1.571", 
            "start": "48.289"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "One at a time, grab a noodle on both ends and bend it until it breaks.", 
            "dur": "3.748", 
            "start": "49.86"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You&#39;ll notice that the majority of the noodles break into more than two pieces.", 
            "dur": "3.688", 
            "start": "53.608"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now you might not think this is a big deal.", 
            "dur": "2.099", 
            "start": "57.296"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But it&#39;s a really big deal.", 
            "dur": "1.944", 
            "start": "59.395"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You see it&#39;s really easy to understand why bending", 
            "dur": "2.727", 
            "start": "61.339"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "a rod makes it break into two pieces.", 
            "dur": "1.86", 
            "start": "64.066"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The bottom is in compression and the top is in tension.", 
            "dur": "2.883", 
            "start": "65.926"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "When the tension on the top exceeds the maximum", 
            "dur": "2.333", 
            "start": "68.809"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "allowable tensile stress, it rips it in half", 
            "dur": "2.419", 
            "start": "71.142"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and you&#39;re left with only two pieces of the rod left.", 
            "dur": "3.199", 
            "start": "73.561"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So why is spaghetti different?", 
            "dur": "2.079", 
            "start": "76.76"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Something else is happening here.", 
            "dur": "1.633", 
            "start": "78.839"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The simple act of snapping spaghetti has stumped", 
            "dur": "2.317", 
            "start": "80.472"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "brilliant scientists for years, including Richard Feynman,", 
            "dur": "2.849", 
            "start": "82.789"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "who as you might know, was on the theoretical physics", 
            "dur": "2.4", 
            "start": "85.638"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "team during the Manhattan Project and also won a", 
            "dur": "1.96", 
            "start": "88.038"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Nobel Prize for Physics in 1965.", 
            "dur": "2.373", 
            "start": "89.998"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Everyone accepts that Richard Feynman was a genius", 
            "dur": "2.185", 
            "start": "92.371"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "so it&#39;s no surprise that his theory about why", 
            "dur": "2.207", 
            "start": "94.556"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "spaghetti snaps into multiple pieces makes a lot of sense.", 
            "dur": "2.631", 
            "start": "96.763"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you tried it by now yourself, you know that when you snap it", 
            "dur": "2.885", 
            "start": "99.394"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you feel this little vibration in your fingers.", 
            "dur": "2.556", 
            "start": "102.279"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He thought that this vibration, if it was significant enough,", 
            "dur": "2.354", 
            "start": "104.835"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "could excite the remaining spaghetti sufficiently", 
            "dur": "2.526", 
            "start": "107.189"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "so that it would cause a secondary fracture on down the rod.", 
            "dur": "3.523", 
            "start": "109.715"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "To test this theory Feynman and a friend decided to snap", 
            "dur": "2.664", 
            "start": "113.238"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "spaghetti under water to dampen out this vibration.", 
            "dur": "2.696", 
            "start": "115.902"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "They were surprised to find out that when they snapped it under water", 
            "dur": "3.01", 
            "start": "118.598"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it still seemed to break into multiple pieces.", 
            "dur": "2.629", 
            "start": "121.608"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So here we are.", 
            "dur": "1.059", 
            "start": "124.237"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If a smart dude like Richard Feynman can&#39;t figure this out,", 
            "dur": "2.637", 
            "start": "125.296"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "what chance do we have?", 
            "dur": "1.792", 
            "start": "127.933"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So we&#39;re gonna figure this out in my kitchen.", 
            "dur": "1.54", 
            "start": "129.725"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is what we&#39;re doing.", 
            "dur": "1.034", 
            "start": "131.265"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "My wife brought home all kinds of different pasta for me,", 
            "dur": "3.569", 
            "start": "132.299"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "at my request.", 
            "dur": "1.135", 
            "start": "135.868"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;ve got them taken out here and we&#39;re running an experiment", 
            "dur": "2.726", 
            "start": "137.003"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "with this high speed camera, it&#39;s a Phantom V1610.", 
            "dur": "3.428", 
            "start": "139.729"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We have a lamp set up and we&#39;re just gonna sit and", 
            "dur": "3.239", 
            "start": "143.157"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "break pasta and observe.", 
            "dur": "1.795", 
            "start": "146.396"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I looked all over the internet and the fastest research imagery I could find", 
            "dur": "3.814", 
            "start": "148.191"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "was 4000 frames per second.", 
            "dur": "2.019", 
            "start": "152.005"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So in order to further science,", 
            "dur": "1.632", 
            "start": "154.024"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we&#39;re gonna start out at at least 18,000 frames per second.", 
            "dur": "3.405", 
            "start": "155.656"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Which surely should tell us something right?", 
            "dur": "1.729", 
            "start": "159.061"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[slowed snap]", 
            "dur": "1.504", 
            "start": "162.72"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Woah.", 
            "dur": "0.762", 
            "start": "166.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That was fast.", 
            "dur": "1.09", 
            "start": "167.059"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "OK I couldn&#39;t even tell which fracture happened first.", 
            "dur": "2.58", 
            "start": "168.149"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We&#39;ll zoom it back in and go frame by frame.", 
            "dur": "2.97", 
            "start": "170.729"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[snap]", 
            "dur": "0.976", 
            "start": "174.909"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Yeah it&#39;s way too fast.", 
            "dur": "1.693", 
            "start": "176.259"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Both fractures happen at what seems to be the same time.", 
            "dur": "3.306", 
            "start": "178.421"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s look at another piece that breaks up even more", 
            "dur": "2.108", 
            "start": "181.727"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and see if it sheds some light into what&#39;s going on here.", 
            "dur": "2.536", 
            "start": "183.835"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[snap]", 
            "dur": "1.406", 
            "start": "187.089"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What?!", 
            "dur": "1.021", 
            "start": "189.294"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s like all the fracture points are happening at the exact", 
            "dur": "2.202", 
            "start": "190.315"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "same time which is crazy because we&#39;re well below a", 
            "dur": "2.54", 
            "start": "192.517"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "millisecond time scale here.", 
            "dur": "1.934", 
            "start": "195.057"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;m not really sure what the researchers were seeing", 
            "dur": "2.239", 
            "start": "196.991"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "at 4000 frames per second, but I&#39;m not seeing it.", 
            "dur": "2.207", 
            "start": "199.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So let&#39;s bump this thing up to 40,000 frames per second", 
            "dur": "3.665", 
            "start": "201.467"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which is ten times faster than any research paper I&#39;ve read.", 
            "dur": "2.752", 
            "start": "205.132"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[snap]", 
            "dur": "1.154", 
            "start": "209.484"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Hmm. OK so we&#39;re starting to learn something.", 
            "dur": "2.023", 
            "start": "213.977"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I can at least tell that the right side broke first.", 
            "dur": "2.725", 
            "start": "216"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But both still seemed to be happening within 100 microseconds", 
            "dur": "2.335", 
            "start": "218.725"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of each other, which is really really fast.", 
            "dur": "2.467", 
            "start": "221.06"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Also, let&#39;s start to watch the rotation direction of the broken pieces.", 
            "dur": "3.233", 
            "start": "223.922"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s watch another one and see if vibration has anything", 
            "dur": "3.179", 
            "start": "227.155"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to do with that second fracture.", 
            "dur": "1.664", 
            "start": "230.334"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[snap]", 
            "dur": "1.964", 
            "start": "233.432"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "No.", 
            "dur": "0.669", 
            "start": "237.557"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In fact it appears that the longer rods aren&#39;t even", 
            "dur": "2.2", 
            "start": "238.226"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "vibrating on the same time scale.", 
            "dur": "2.225", 
            "start": "240.426"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Here&#39;s something though.", 
            "dur": "1.175", 
            "start": "242.651"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you look, the smaller broken pieces when they start to rotate,", 
            "dur": "2.875", 
            "start": "243.826"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "always seem to rotate away from the first fracture.", 
            "dur": "3.567", 
            "start": "246.701"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The back however appears to be breaking downwards.", 
            "dur": "3.113", 
            "start": "250.268"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s almost as if the spaghetti is trying to straighten itself out", 
            "dur": "2.913", 
            "start": "253.381"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but it can&#39;t overcome its own mass.", 
            "dur": "2.502", 
            "start": "256.294"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Buckle your seatbelt cause we&#39;re going to a quarter million", 
            "dur": "2.499", 
            "start": "258.796"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "frames per second.", 
            "dur": "1.341", 
            "start": "261.295"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[snap]", 
            "dur": "2.345", 
            "start": "264.916"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Man, we had to go way faster than I thought we would to get this answer", 
            "dur": "3.594", 
            "start": "268.667"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but there it is.", 
            "dur": "1.029", 
            "start": "272.261"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I mean it&#39;s not vibration.", 
            "dur": "1.6", 
            "start": "273.29"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s the curvature of the spaghetti as it straightens out.", 
            "dur": "3.272", 
            "start": "274.89"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Think about it this way.", 
            "dur": "1.759", 
            "start": "278.162"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The entire spaghetti rod is under torque, right?", 
            "dur": "2.608", 
            "start": "279.921"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Because of this torque, it bends in a curve.", 
            "dur": "2.498", 
            "start": "282.529"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And when a break occurs, the side near the break is now", 
            "dur": "2.641", 
            "start": "285.027"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "free from torque.", 
            "dur": "1.491", 
            "start": "287.668"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But there&#39;s still this counter-torque built up in the rod.", 
            "dur": "3.011", 
            "start": "289.159"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So it starts to straighten itself out from left to right,", 
            "dur": "2.888", 
            "start": "292.17"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "rotating up and straightening out along the way.", 
            "dur": "2.812", 
            "start": "295.058"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Because the spaghetti on the left is already straightened out", 
            "dur": "1.999", 
            "start": "297.87"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and the spaghetti on the right is still curved,", 
            "dur": "1.697", 
            "start": "299.869"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the point where they meet is now even more curved,", 
            "dur": "2.47", 
            "start": "301.566"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which causes the spaghetti to bend beyond the minimum failure radius.", 
            "dur": "3.365", 
            "start": "304.036"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This results in a fracture.", 
            "dur": "1.634", 
            "start": "307.401"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s like one side doesn&#39;t get the message fast enough.", 
            "dur": "2.627", 
            "start": "309.035"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If the whole rod were to release at one time it&#39;d be fine,", 
            "dur": "3.304", 
            "start": "311.662"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but it doesn&#39;t.", 
            "dur": "0.866", 
            "start": "314.966"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It breaks itself apart along the way.", 
            "dur": "2.532", 
            "start": "315.832"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Every time you have a new break the process starts all over again.", 
            "dur": "2.601", 
            "start": "318.364"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This physical phenomenon is called a cascading fracture.", 
            "dur": "4.096", 
            "start": "320.965"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Until recently the math behind this phenomenon wasn&#39;t", 
            "dur": "2.145", 
            "start": "325.061"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "very well understood.", 
            "dur": "1.484", 
            "start": "327.206"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But I did find a really cool French research paper on the topic", 
            "dur": "3.119", 
            "start": "328.69"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "as well as a neat simulation created by some Norwegian petroleum engineers.", 
            "dur": "3.995", 
            "start": "331.809"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "To my knowledge though, the video that we just watched gives more insight", 
            "dur": "3.658", 
            "start": "335.804"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "into this physical phenomenon than anything else that&#39;s ever been done.", 
            "dur": "3.109", 
            "start": "339.462"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We just did it at a quarter of a million frames per second,", 
            "dur": "3.052", 
            "start": "342.571"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which is amazing.", 
            "dur": "0.831", 
            "start": "345.623"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So there you go.", 
            "dur": "1.242", 
            "start": "346.454"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The secret of snapping spaghetti is not just a party trick.", 
            "dur": "3.205", 
            "start": "347.696"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The next time you boil spaghetti,", 
            "dur": "1.802", 
            "start": "350.901"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "be careful because you are about to explore the very edge", 
            "dur": "3.361", 
            "start": "352.703"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of scientific knowledge.", 
            "dur": "1.868", 
            "start": "356.064"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So thank you very much for watching this episode of Smarter Every Day.", 
            "dur": "3.005", 
            "start": "357.935"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you would like to get a book that talks about all the things", 
            "dur": "2.856", 
            "start": "360.94"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that Richard Feynman studied, I recommend an Audible book", 
            "dur": "3.174", 
            "start": "363.796"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "called Surely You&#39;re Joking Mr Feynman.", 
            "dur": "2.723", 
            "start": "366.97"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;m listening to it right now and it&#39;s really good.", 
            "dur": "3.112", 
            "start": "369.693"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you would like to support Smarter Every Day", 
            "dur": "1.54", 
            "start": "372.805"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "go to Audible.com/smarter and download", 
            "dur": "3.017", 
            "start": "374.345"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Surely You&#39;re Joking Mr Feynman and you would", 
            "dur": "2.608", 
            "start": "377.362"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "support Smarter Every Day and I would", 
            "dur": "1.395", 
            "start": "379.97"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "greatly appreciate that.", 
            "dur": "1.178", 
            "start": "381.365"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So thank you very much.", 
            "dur": "0.97", 
            "start": "382.543"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;m Destin,", 
            "dur": "1.023", 
            "start": "383.513"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you&#39;re getting Smarter Every Day,", 
            "dur": "1.322", 
            "start": "384.536"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "have a good one.", 
            "dur": "1.471", 
            "start": "385.858"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "(kid) Woo!", 
            "dur": "0.834", 
            "start": "387.329"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "(Destin) You ever heard of Richard Feynman?", 
            "dur": "1.029", 
            "start": "388.163"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "(Kids) No. No idea.", 
            "dur": "1.535", 
            "start": "389.192"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "- No idea?", 
            "dur": "0.896", 
            "start": "390.727"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "- I have no idea who he is but it sounds fine.", 
            "dur": "3.239", 
            "start": "391.623"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "- [laughs] Well he is.", 
            "dur": "1.671", 
            "start": "394.862"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He&#39;s a little different than daddy but he&#39;s a pretty smart awesome dude.", 
            "dur": "4.501", 
            "start": "396.533"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Three.", 
            "dur": "1.076", 
            "start": "402.404"
        }, 
